  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Education Cluster Flood Response in Malawi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this UNICEF is to provide education support for flood affected households. UNICEF will ensure that 51,300 children in 4 affected districts have access to quality teaching and learning materials. UNICEF will procure 670 school in a box kits and 570 recreation kits for the affected districts. Students will also be provided with psychosocial support through the deployment of 72 teachers to support the interventions. Some 51,300 children will be assisted over 3 months.</narrative>
  </description>
